f=Engineering/aegis/custom/vuln-pipeline/assets/findings-schema.md · h1:Vulnerability Findings Schema aegis/vuln-pipeline=Adapted defending-code harness's VULN-FINDINGS.json TRIAGE.json shape (credit: anthropics/defending-code-reference-harness), bound department's routing threat model. One row unique, verified finding. · fi:s table=\| id \| title \| threat_id \| location \| class \| severity \| confidence \| verified \| status \| owner \| routed_to \| · fi:s table=\|---\|---\|---\|---\|---\|---\|---\|---\|---\|---\|---\| · fi:s table=`id`: `F1`, `F2`, stable across triage passes., `title`: one line, names concrete vulnerability (`dr_wav.h:412 unchecked chunk_size heap overflow`)., `threat_id`: THREAT_MODEL.md threat instantiates (`T1`). matching threat threat-model gap, flagged., `location`: `file:line` component; harness's precise-locus discipline., `class`: OWASP CWE category (injection, authz, memory, SSRF, secrets, crypto, deserialization…)., `severity`: recalibrated business's assets `low\|medium\|high\|critical` (threat-model impact reachability)., `confidence`: `static-only` `execution-verified` (separate grader reproduced it)., `verified`: reproduced-in-fresh-env? `yes\|no`. `no` candidate, finding route downstream., `status`: `open patching patched-unverified closed` (closed verified-patching regression-map entry)., `owner`: owning builder dev's domain routing., `routed_to`: quinn intake ref verified-patching ref owner notification. · h2:Dropped (audit trail false positives out-of-scope)=\| candidate \| reason \| · h2:Dropped (audit trail false positives out-of-scope)=\|---\|---\| · h2:Dropped (audit trail false positives out-of-scope)=\| \| test/fixture code \· unreachable \· duplicate of F# \· unverified after N attempts \· risk-accepted by owner \| · h2:Provenance=scoped_by: [THREAT_MODEL.md path ref], mode: static \| execution(sandboxed), date: YYYY-MM-DD, source: pipeline scan dev risky-diff referral ops CVE handoff [CVE id]